</p>

# Creating HTML Numbered Lists
HTML is lists- ordered and unordered. Ordered lists use numbers while Unordered lists use bullet points. So, anytime you want to have an ordered list of items, use 
the tag <ol>, and list each element within a nested <li> tag.

<div>
  <ol>
    <li>My first point</li>
    <li>My second point</li>
    <li>My third point</li>
  </ol>
</div>

Example: 

<div>
  <ol>
    <li>My first point, with <a href="http//yahoo.com">reference materials</a></li>
    <li>My second point</li>
    <li>My third point</li>
  </ol>
</div>

# Bullet Point Lists in HTML
To do this, we will use a tag called <ul> which stands for unordered list. Inside this tag, we will list out elements with the <li> tag, same as coding ordered 
lists.

<div>
  <ul>
    <li>My first point, with <a href="http//yahoo.com">reference materials</a></li>
    <li>My second point</li>
    <li>My third point</li>
  </ul>
</div>

# Bold HTML Styles
As always, let's create a <div>, and put a paragraph of text inside. To make the first word bold, just add a <b> tag and close it off after "Lorem".

<div>
 <p>
   <b>Lorem</b> ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure <br>dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum.
 </p>
</div>

Alternately, you can also use a tag called <strong> instead of <b>. If you refresh the browser, both the tags will produce identical results. However, there is a 
subtle difference between the two. The <b> tag simply shows the content inside of its tag in bold, whereas <strong> is used to emphasize a specific word.

# Italic Style for Text
<i>Duis</i>

# List of HTML Style Tags
- Unordered: 
<ul>
  <li></li>
</ul>

- Mark:
<ul>
  <li>The <mark>marked</mark> text tag</li>
</ul>

- Small:
<li>The <small>small</small> text tag</li>

- Deleted:
<li>The <del>deleted</del> text tag</li>

- Inserted:
<li>The <ins>inserted</ins> text tag</li>

- Subscript:
<li>The <sub>subscript</sub> text tag</li>

- Superscript:
<li>The <sup>superscript</sup> text tag</li>

- Pre style:
<li>The <pre>pre</pre> text tag</li>

- Quotation:
<li>The <q>quotation</q> text tag</li>

